[[!meta title="Numerous security holes in T(A)ILS 0.5"]]
[[!pagetemplate template="news.tmpl"]]

[[!tag security/fixed]]

The following security holes affect T(A)ILS 0.5.

We **strongly** urge you to [[upgrade to T(A)ILS
0.6|news/version_0.6]] in case you are still using an older version.

  - avahi: DSA-2086-1
  - bzip2: DSA-2112-1
  - freetype: DSA-2105-1, DSA-2070-1, DSA-2116-1
  - git-core: DSA-2114-1
  - glibc, eglibc: DSA-2058-1
  - ghostscript: DSA-2093-1, DSA-2080-1
  - lvm2: DSA-2095-1
  - libpng: DSA-2072-1
  - linux-2.6: DSA-2110-1, DSA-2094-1, DSA-2053-1
  - openoffice.org: DSA-2099-1, DSA-2055-1
  - openssl: DSA-2100-1
  - pcsc-lite: DSA-2059-1
  - pmount: DSA-2063-1
  - poppler: DSA-2119-1
  - smbind: DSA-2103-1
  - sudo: DSA-2062-1
  - libtheora: DSA-2045-1
  - tiff: DSA-2084-1
  - wget: DSA-2088-1
  - xulrunner: DSA-2106-1, DSA-2075-1, DSA-2064-1

These are Debian security announces; details can be found on
<http://security.debian.org/>.
